# Shared UI Primitives

Before adding or changing UI, inspect:

- `templates/_ui_macros.html`
- `templates/_inventory_macros.html`
- `templates/_item_macros.html`
- `static/css/styles.css`
- `UI_COMPONENTS.md`

Required behavior:

- Use `ui.page_header` for page headers before building a custom title/action block.
- Use `ui.toolbar` and shared control classes for search/filter/sort/action layouts.
- Use shared chips/state helpers instead of Bootstrap badge drift.
- Use `ui.form_section` for structured settings/admin forms unless the page already has a stronger shared pattern.
- Use shared empty/loading/banner/validation states instead of one-off alerts or dashed boxes.

Reject:

- New page-local header systems
- New badge systems
- One-off control-height or spacing hacks when shared classes/tokens already exist
